	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="100" facs="EHRI-ET-SOV004_100.jpg"/>
			<p><term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Fascist</term>
				<q>Humor</q></p>

			<p>Told by <persName ref="#ehri_et_broderzon_moyshe">M. Broderzon</persName></p>

			<p>in: The Blood Cries for Vengeance!: What Victims tell about the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Fascist</term> Atrocities in
				the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-632" type="subject">Occupied</term>
				<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName>, collected and assembled by <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_kvitko_leyb">L. Kvitko</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_nusinov_yitskhok">Y. Nusinov</persName>, and <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_katsnelson">Y. Katsnelson</persName>; Forword: <persName ref="#ehri_et_epshteyn_shakhne">Shakhne Epshteyn</persName>
					(<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/524901/moscow.html">Moscow</placeName>: Der Emes, <date when="1941">1941</date>), pp.
				100–104</p>

			<p>In <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3093133/lodz.html">Łódź</placeName>, like in all other cities, the civilian Jewish
				population was snapped up for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term>. Whilst
				catching them for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> and during the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> itself, the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hitlerites</term>
				<q><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-555" type="subject">made fun</term></q> of the wretched people, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-599" type="subject">teared out beards</term> of Jews together with pieces
				of their chins, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-555" type="subject">ridiculed them</term>, kicked them
				with their feet. In this, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-555" type="subject">humorous spirit</term>
				of the cannibals was already expressed. It was their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-555" type="subject"
					>entertainment</term>, their pleasure. I came across such facts of <q>humor</q> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/798544/republic-of-poland.html">Poland</placeName> a lot.</p>
			<p>In general, the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hitlerites</term> love to take <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject">photographs</term>, i.e. to stage-manage different
				images and to pronounce them as <q><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject"
						>photo-documents</term>.</q> These fake <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject"
					>photographies</term> constitute a dirty weapon of <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000152"
					>Goebbels’</persName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-986" type="subject">propaganda</term>.</p>
			<p>In front of my eyes, the following episode took place. A large number of Jews were rounded up, forced to wrap themselves in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">taleysim</term>
				<note place="bottom">prayer shawls.</note> and to sway. A <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701"
					type="subject">photographer</term> came to the site, who preserved this <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject">image</term>.</p>
			<p>Afterwards, it was shown around abroad.</p>
			<p>Why was this done?</p>
			<p>First, in order to prove what a savage, Asiatic people the Jews are – they pray in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">taleysim</term> and sway during prayers like madmen…
				And second, they wanted to prove to the pious, tender-hearted <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_americans">Americans</term> that Jews
				are living a good life under the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> – they are allowed to pray as much as they
				want…</p>
			<p><persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000185">Hitler</persName>’s <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-986" type="subject">propagandists</term> did not tell anyone, though,
				about <pb n="101" facs="EHRI-ET-SOV004_101.jpg"/> the horrific fact that these very Jews who they had first taken <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject">photos</term> of, were arranged in rows immediately
				after the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject">photo-session</term> and… <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">shot to death</term>.</p>
			<p>I was also told that in many <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Polish</term> shtetlekh the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-555" type="subject">entertained</term> themselves with placing <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-735" type="subject">rabbis</term> on <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-555" type="subject">wodden mares in the middle of the market
				square</term>. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-735" type="subject">rabbis</term>
				<q><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-555" type="subject">were riding</term>,</q> dressed in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">shtraymlekh</term>
				<note place="bottom">round fur hat worn by orthodox Jews on the Sabbath and holidays.</note> on their heads, and old chassidim were
				standing beside them with brooms in their hands…</p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-735" type="subject">rabbi</term> had to hold a banner in his hand
				with the inscription:</p>
			<p><q>We, the damned Jews, wanted the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080" type="subject"
				>war</term>.</q></p>
			<p>In the language of the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> this equals… humor and satire.</p>
			<p>And here we have another example for their bandit-like humor.</p>
			<p>One day, an old acquainted <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-899" type="subject">Jewish lawyer</term> was
				snapped up for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/3093133/lodz.html">Łódź</placeName>. He was weak, nearsighted <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">man</term>. So he was sent to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work…</term> to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">carry coals from one spot to another and
				back</term>.</p>
			<p>Once this <q><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term></q> was done, the
				quartermaster was looking for a more complex occupation for him. He drags him up to the roof of the four-story building and forces
				him… to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">clean up the chimney</term> with his
				hands.</p>
			<p>When the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-899" type="subject">lawyer</term> was smeared with soot from
				head to toe, a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject">photographer</term> showed up
				unexpectedly, who had to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-701" type="subject">immortalize the
					image</term>.</p>
			<p>After that, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-899" type="subject">lawyer</term>, dirty as he was, was
				placed in front of the wall and ordered to laugh…</p>
			<p>– You should laugh Jewishly! – the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hitlerite</term> commanded.</p>
			<p>The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">tortured</term><term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-899" type="subject">lawyer</term> did not understand what to <q>laugh
					Jewishly</q> means. So the quartermaster goes up to his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-132"
					type="subject">victim</term>, sticks in two <q><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject"
						>Aryan</term></q> fingers into his mouth, rips open his lips and… takes a picture.</p>
			<p>The representatives of the <q><term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373" type="subject">chosen race</term></q>
				did the following in the shtetl <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/755474/wlodawa.html">Włodawa</placeName>:</p>
			<p>They spread an announcement that tomorrow at 7am sharp all old, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292"
					type="subject">sick</term> and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-326" type="subject">disabled
					people</term> from the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/755474/wlodawa.html">shtetl</placeName> are summoned to come and
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-647" type="subject">register</term> – they will be sent to the
				sanatorium.</p>
			<p><pb n="102" facs="EHRI-ET-SOV004_102.jpg"/> On the next day, at 7am sharp, approximately 200 <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> come and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-647" type="subject">register</term>. They are all <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-326" type="subject">disabled</term>, <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-292" type="subject">sick</term> and old people. They were arranged in a
				line, and with the help of machine guns… they are sent away to the mentioned <q>sanatorium</q>, from which <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">no one ever comes back</term>.</p>
			<p>Their <q>humor</q> has a diabolic nature.</p>
			<p>On some Friday, 25 Jews were snapped up for <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject"
					>work</term> in broad daylight.</p>
			<p>The Jews are standing outside guarded by a sentinel and wait. They wait for a very long time.</p>
			<p>Then, a <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldier</term> exits the building in a blindingly
				white apron and commands that one Jew of the 25 shall come with him.</p>
			<p>It takes two minutes and the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldier</term> comes
				back out again on his own… but with his apron soaked in blood, with bloody hands… He commands a second Jew to follow him
				immediately.</p>
			<p>This makes a terrifying impression on the Jews. They go cold and are seized by a saddening <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">deathly</term> fear. One of them goes insane on the
				spot, others lose consciousness, one <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject">dies</term>
				there from a heart attack. The others one after the other followed that same <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldier</term> inside.</p>
			<p>It turns out that the only thing this sadistic procedure consisted of was that the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldier</term> slaughtered geese and he called upon
				the Jews to pluck the down from feathers...</p>
			<p>The young female <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">physician</term> Sh. was ordered to
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">clean the toilets</term> at the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-940" type="subject">train</term> station with her hands. She did it. The
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldier</term> was not pleased with her <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term>, however. So he gives her a bucket with
				hydrochloric acid and a rag and orders her to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">clean
					the toilets</term> with it. From the hydrochloric acid, the young <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">girl’s</term> hands are burning. She cries
				bitterly…</p>
			<p>Then, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldier</term> takes the rag, immerses it
				into the hydrochloric acid and wipes off the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject"
					>physician’s</term> tears with it… together with her eyes.</p>
			<p>More than once did it come to pass that I as well as hundreds of unfortunate Jews had to walk around aimlessly, without purpose, for
				dozens of kilometres because this is what the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hilterite</term> blood suckers wanted.</p>
			<p><pb n="103" facs="EHRI-ET-SOV004_103.jpg"/> For them, it was a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562"
					type="subject">game, a spiritual pleasure, an entertainment</term>, and we felt as if our hearts were falling out. As if our knees
				become weak. And the more tired we were, the more reckless their state was, all the more they <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-555" type="subject">ridiculed</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-562" type="subject">tortured</term> us. When we were running (in their
				language this is called <q>gymnastics</q>), they were chasing us with sticks and revolvers in their hands. They were very violent.</p>
			<p>– Hop-hop, damned Jews! Run! Run!</p>

			<p>***</p>
			<p>On a cold autumn day, we drove to the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_soviets">Soviet</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-234" type="subject">border</term>. We ran away from the bloody <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hitlerite</term> axe.</p>
			<p>When our truck travelled for some time from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/760684/radzymin.html">Radzymin</placeName> (near
					<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>), three armed <persName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000185">Hitler</persName>-<term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldiers</term> stopped us.</p>
			<p>– Stop, stand still! – They were screaming out loud.</p>
			<p>Our car stopped.</p>
			<p>– <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">Men</term>, out!</p>
			<p>So the ten <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">men</term> disembarked and took out the
				luggage.</p>
			<p>The famous <q>inspection</q> of the luggage started. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject"
					>They immediately took several things from it</term>. After that, they did individual inspections. One of the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hitlerites</term> examines me. Where is, I am supposed to tell him, the rifle which I <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hide</term> from the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject">soldiers</term>? The <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term> is not able to find any rifle on me. But looking at my warm <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836" type="subject">coat</term> which I wear, he says with a smile:</p>
			<p>– You are cold, right? Don’t worry, you will be warm soon…</p>
			<p>Naturally, as soon as I heard this, I got very warm.</p>
			<p>This characteristic episode ended in the following way: the eldest of the three commanded that we place our things on the car while we
				stay below. He further commanded the driver to drive 100 metres.</p>
			<p>When all of this was done, he slowly took out a gun from his case, pointed at us and suddenly barked at us.</p>
			<p>– Damned Jews, run! The last one will be <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-536" type="subject"
				>shot</term>!</p>
			<p>And ten Jews, grown-ups, elderlies, started running like crazy…</p>
			<p>Of our belongings, we did not see any of it anymore, of course… We were nonetheless happy that we managed to <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204" type="subject">escape</term> from the <term
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Hitlerite</term> hell alive...</p>
